content.text:
`isActive` is not set in `navConfig.ts`; that file only defines static nav metadata.

Itâ€™s derived in `AuthenticatedAppShell.tsx` from the current route path:

```tsx
const isNavItemActive = (itemUrl: string, pathname: string) => {
  const pattern = itemUrl === "/requests" ? "/requests/*" : itemUrl;
  return Boolean(matchPath({ path: pattern, end: itemUrl !== "/requests" }, pathname));
};
```

Then itâ€™s applied when mapping nav groups into sidebar props:

```tsx
isActive: isNavItemActive(item.url, pathname),
```

So for the selected line:

```tsx
{ key: "requests", title: "Aanvragen", url: "/requests", icon: FileEditIcon as IconSvgElement }
```

`Aanvragen` becomes active for `/requests`, `/requests/create`, `/requests/:id`, and `/requests/:id/edit`.
